│                                                                               │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash is caused by an assertion in                                        │
│ LoopVectorizationPlanner::computeBestVF that checks consistency between the   │
│ legacy cost model and the new VPlan-based cost model. The assertion allows    │
│ disagreement only if the chosen VPlan contains additional simplifications not │
│ accounted for by the legacy cost model. In this reproducer, the two models    │
│ disagree, but the check falsely concludes that the VPlan does not contain     │
│ additional simplifications and thus triggers the assertion.                   │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log:                                                     │
│ The failure happens in computeBestVF around the assertion that compares       │
│ BestFactor.Width with LegacyVF.Width. The supporting helper                   │
│ planContainsAdditionalSimplifications is intended to detect when the VPlan    │
│ removes or simplifies certain IR (e.g., control flow like IV increment, exit  │
│ checks, branches) that the legacy cost model still accounts for. If such      │
│ extra simplifications are present, the assertion is suppressed. However, the  │
│ current implementation incorrectly marks some original loop instructions to   │
│ be ignored for cost computation, causing                                      │
│ planContainsAdditionalSimplifications to return false.                        │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ In planContainsAdditionalSimplifications, the predicate used to determine     │
│ extra simplifications excludes PHIs in the header (correct) and relies on     │
│ CostCtx.skipCostComputation(&I, true) to decide whether an original           │
│ instruction should be ignored. Passing `IsVector=true` makes                  │
│ VPCostContext::skipCostComputation consult both CM.ValuesToIgnore and         │
│ CM.VecValuesToIgnore. The latter can include control-flow and other           │
│ scalar-only instructions when computing vector costs, effectively masking the │
│ fact that the VPlan has removed/simplified those original IR constructs. As a │
│ result, planContainsAdditionalSimplifications returns false even when the     │
│ VPlan has indeed simplified away such instructions, which leads to the        │
│ assertion firing.                                                             │
│                                                                               │
│ To correctly detect extra simplifications,                                    │
│ planContainsAdditionalSimplifications should be conservative and not use the  │
│ vector-specific ignore set. It should only consult the general ignore set for │
│ values that the legacy cost-model truly ignores altogether. Using             │
│ `IsVector=false` ensures control-flow and scalar-only instructions remaining  │
│ in the original loop but absent from the VPlan are treated as evidence of     │
│ extra simplifications.                                                        │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp                       │
│ - Location: in planContainsAdditionalSimplifications, change the call to      │
│ skipCostComputation to pass IsVector=false.                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ Edit:                                                                         │
│ Lines 7419-7422:                                                              │
│ Old:                                                                          │
│       if (isa<PHINode>(&I) && BB == TheLoop->getHeader())                     │
│         return false;                                                         │
│       return !SeenInstrs.contains(&I) && !CostCtx.skipCostComputation(&I,     │
│ true);                                                                        │
│ New:                                                                          │
│       if (isa<PHINode>(&I) && BB == TheLoop->getHeader())                     │
│         return false;                                                         │
│       // Use non-vector ignore set to conservatively detect extra             │
│ simplifications.                                                              │
│       return !SeenInstrs.contains(&I) && !CostCtx.skipCostComputation(&I,     │
│ false);                                                                       │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ By making planContainsAdditionalSimplifications consult only the non-vector   │
│ ignore set, we properly detect when the VPlan eliminates or simplifies        │
│ original loop IR (such as control flow) that the legacy model still counts.   │
│ This causes planContainsAdditionalSimplifications to return true in such      │
│ cases, preventing the assertion from triggering when the cost models disagree │
│ due to legitimate VPlan simplifications. The fix is local, safe under NDEBUG  │
│ (debug-only code), and aligns with the intended purpose of the check.         │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
│                                                                               │
